    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="184"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1354.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 21, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 7th instant, No. 917,
                    relative to the manner in which you have deemed it expedient to address her
                    Majesty’s government in protesting against their course in continuing to
                    recognize the insurgents as belligerents, has been received.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c., London.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
